    "## 8. Conclusions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Findings:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **A\\*** is fastest but produces paths that don't respect vehicle kinematics\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Hybrid A\\*** provides a good balance between speed and path quality\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **RRT\\*** handles complex environments well but with higher variance\n",
    "\n",
    "### Recommendations:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Use **Hybrid A\\*** for standard lunar navigation tasks\n",
    "- Use **RRT\\*** when exploring unknown or complex terrain\n",
    "- Use **A\\*** for quick baseline comparisons and simple environments"
   ]
